 also developing concepts for makerspace design. This volume is the first systematic study of these developments, exploring concepts such as how the learning environment can be structured as a makerspace.  aMakerspaces entwickeln sich (stark inspiriert aus dem anglo-amerikanischen Kontext) zu einer neuen Art von Lehr- und Lernräumen. Neben der außerinstitutionellen Makerbewegung entwickeln unter anderem Hochschulen und Bibliotheken Konzepte zur Gestaltung von Makerspaces. In diesem Band werden diese Entwicklungen erstmalig grundlegend systematisiert und Konzepte vorgestellt, wie sich die Lernwelt „Makerspace" konturiert.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aMakerspace. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / School Media.2bisacsh1 aDobeleit, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbner, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarding, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinzel, Viktoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinzel, Viktoria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHollauf, Eva-Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJastram, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöble, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLange, Bastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLinke, Hanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuga, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMerkel, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt, Suntje, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc